{"questionId":"22013","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>It is known that the weights of male Persian cats are normally distributed with mean <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>kg</mtext></math>&nbsp;and variance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>kg</mtext><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Sketch a diagram showing the above information.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/3ebc1702a6994c9883284ce0c41f5f9992157423.png\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for a normal curve with mean labelled <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi></math>, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for indication of SD <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>:</mo></math> marks on horizontal axis at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math> and/or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;<strong>OR</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math> and/or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math> on the correct side and approximately correct position.<br><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22013","referenceCode":"21M.2.AHL.TZ2.2a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Sketch a diagram showing the above information.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"